# Execution rules — Calm Corner bundle

You are executing CURSOR-PROMPT.md in this folder. It is a pre-decided, pre-researched plan.

1. Follow CURSOR-PROMPT.md literally, phases in order. No redesigns, no extra dependencies, no repos beyond the six listed (ffalt/mah, gabrielecirulli/2048, mmenavas/memory-game, michaelbutler/minesweeper, bunkat/wordfind, kbjorklu/chess).
2. The hub (index.html), DESIGN-SPEC.md, and games/charades, games/draw-guess, games/impostor are FINISHED. Do not recreate, restyle, or "improve" them. Only permitted edits there: remove cards/credits of dropped games; replace __ISSUES_URL__.
3. Timeboxes are binding: a fetched game that exceeds its fix budget gets dropped (delete folder + remove hub card + credits line + note in SHIP-REPORT.md). Ship what works.
4. Never modify or remove upstream LICENSE files. Only permitted in-game edits: mahjong <base href> fix, chess.html -> index.html rename, and the Lobby-button snippet.
5. Any visual work follows DESIGN-SPEC.md tokens exactly. No new colors, fonts, or spacing values.
6. Shell is Windows PowerShell. The repo root is the website root.
7. Log every test result in TESTLOG.md and every deviation in SHIP-REPORT.md.
8. Do not mention "Vita" anywhere in the product or repo.
9. Definition of done: live GitHub Pages URL, >=7 playable games, credits complete, SHIP-REPORT.md written. Then stop.
